# Git branch

- **Default branch: `master`** — commit and push feature work here unless the user says otherwise.
- Before editing: `git switch master` (or `git pull origin master`).
- After commits: `git push origin master`.
- Branch `features` may exist historically; do not switch to it unless the user asks.

See `AGENTS.md` for full workflow.
